race.comment: BLUISH HUE (8) had been improving with racing and that culminated with a strong Toowoomba victory last time out. Maps perfectly for this from gate two and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. THE STARS (13) resumes here but brings NSW formlines to the table and should find this a touch easier. Can run a big race while fresh. BELIEVE IN ANGELS (3) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and will run his usual honest race. BOLD BIDDER (9) tends to mix his form but improved last start to finish second over 1120m at Lismore. Has claims on best. LUMENS LENNY (6) resumes and can contest.
